JENKINS INSTALLATION ON UBUNTU
Step 1: Update the system .
$ sudo apt-get update
Step 2: Install open jdk 8 in your system.
$ sudo apt install openjdk-8-jdk
Step 3: Run the following command to add the repository key to the system.
wget -q -O - https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian/jenkins.io.key | sudo apt-key add -
Step 4: The following command will append the Debian package repository address to your server's
sources.list
$ sudo sh -c 'echo deb http://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/ >
/etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list'
Step 5: Again, update the system.
$ sudo apt update
Step 6: Install Jenkins.
$ sudo apt install jenkins
Congratulations! You have successfully setup Jenkins in your system.
